ugh it is now somewhat out of favour."]},{"name":"Vivian","meanings":["Originally a boy's name, from an Old French form of the Latin name <i>Vivianus</i> (probably a derivative of <i>vivus</i> ‘alive’), but now more frequent as a girl's name. The name was borne by a 5th-century bishop of Saintes in western France, remembered for protecting his people during the invasion of the Visigoths."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Wauthier II de Fontaine-l'Evêque was born in 1085 as the son of Gilles de Fontaines and Prelende Leernes. He had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with Marie de Zottegem."},"et":{"1085–":"1085–Surnud","1085–Male":"1085–Surnud","–1144":"–1144","1100–1144":"1100–1144","1109–Female":"1109–Surnud","1112–1183":"1112–1183","–1096":"–1096","–Female":"Surnud","environ 1100":"umbes 1100","1112":"1112","1100":"1100","1144":"1144","1085":"1085","1096":"1096","1183":"1183","1109":"1109","Conde, Calvados, France":"Conde-sur-Ifs, Calvados, Basse-Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1085–":"1085–Kuollut","1085–Male":"1085–Kuollut","–1144":"–1144","1100–1144":"1100–1144","1109–Female":"1109–Kuollut","1112–1183":"1112–1183","–1096":"–1096","–Female":"Kuollut","environ 1100":"noin 1100","1112":"1112","1100":"1100","1144":"1144","1085":"1085","1096":"1096","1183":"1183","1109":"1109","Conde, Calvados, France":"Conde-sur-Ifs, Calvados, Basse-Normandie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1085–":"1085–Décédé","1085–Male":"1085–Décédé","–1144":"–1144","1100–1144":"1100–1144","1109–Female":"1109–Décédée","1112–1183":"1112–1183","–1096":"–1096","–Female":"Décédée","environ 1100":"environ 1100","1112":"1112","1100":"1100","1144":"1144","1085":"1085","1096":"1096","1183":"1183","1109":"1109","Conde, Calvados, France":"Conde-sur-Ifs, Calvados, Basse-Normandie, France","lifeSummary":"Wauthier II de Fontaine-l'Evêque est né en 1085, fils de Gilles de Fontaines et Prelende Leernes. Il a eu au moins 1 fils et 2 filles avec Marie de Zottegem."},"de":{"1085–":"1085–Verstorben","1085–Male":"1085–Verstorben","–1144":"–1144"